    <47705353+swiftraccoon@users.noreply.github.com>

Distributed under GPL-2.0-or-later.

================================================================
Derivation from MMDVMHost (by Jonathan Naylor, G4KLX)
https://github.com/g4klx/MMDVMHost
================================================================

Affected files (in this crate):
    src/capabilities.rs
    src/command.rs
    src/config.rs
    src/hw_type.rs
    src/lib.rs
    src/mode.rs
    src/nak.rs
    src/status.rs
    src/version.rs

These modules reimplement the wire-format codec, command-byte table,
mode enumeration, status-payload parser, version-handshake parser,
NAK reason codes, hardware-type detection, and configuration builder
as described in the upstream files:

    ref/MMDVMHost/Modem.cpp
    ref/MMDVMHost/Modem.h
    ref/MMDVMHost/Defines.h

Copyright (c) 2015-2026 Jonathan Naylor, G4KLX
    (https://github.com/g4klx)

The upstream files enumerated above all carry the GPL-2.0-or-later
header ("either version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any
later version"). This crate therefore inherits the "or later" grant.

MMDVMHost contains a subset of files (17 of 174, notably DStarControl.cpp,
DMRControl.cpp, DMRData.*, DMRSlot.cpp, DMRTA.*, DMRTrellis.*, NXDNControl.cpp,
P25Trellis.*, POCSAGControl.cpp, YSFControl.cpp, YSFPayload.cpp,
Utils.*, Golay24128.cpp, BCH.cpp) that carry a GPL-2.0-only header.
This crate does NOT derive from any of those files; see the file:line
attributions in each module's doc comment for the upstream reference
point. Keeping the derivation confined to the "or later" subset is
what preserves the outgoing "or later" grant.

No code from MMDVMHost is copied verbatim into this crate. The
derivation is documented inline in each affected module via
"//! Mirrors ref/MMDVMHost/<file>:<line>" comments; those pointers
are the audit trail, not copy-paste.

